commit_list.message:
Vertex is now has self-reverential type parameter, which uses as type paremeter for fields in Vertex and Vertex-based classes

This allows to type vertexes (source, destination) inside of Edge, type edges and vertexes inside of Face, and type any other class derived from Vertex, or class which has T: Vertex<T> as a type parameter. This increases convenience in writing client code, due to eliminating previously required down-casting on accessing class fields, such as vertex.edgeList.source. Now types of vertex, and vertex.edgeList.source are the same.

Javadoc fixed and improved.

(cherry picked from commit 018caa2147e4ae674e9a22b577535d092e5b809f)

A new approach to render layers

Now, layer render to the buffer canvas, which size is larger than the size of visible GUI canvas. Visible canvas displays part of buffer canvas. Rendering happens only when data changes, not when a user scrolls the camera. This approach avoids render during mouse move, which is more performant, especially in the Firefox.

Class describes visible chunk scope for the client.
New method ChunkIdGenerator.chunkRow and chunkColumn

Field manager stores visible players and their positions in the BiMap

Thus, a player by position getting as well as a position by player getting takes O(1).

New class SimpleBiMap

The class has an interface similar to Java BiMap<K,V> from Guava. It contains two associative arrays, which reflects key to value and value to key relations. BiMap preserves the uniqueness of its values as well as that of its keys.

NullEndlessFieldChunk describes null value for EntryLockingConcurrentHashMap.

Related keys mechanism, null mock values

Values may be dependant from another value. If value by key 0 needs access to value by key 1, then value by key 1 have to be instantiated first, then we postpone instantiating of value by key 0 until value by key 1 not attempted to instantiate.  That is, any key has set of related keys, which affects instantiation order.

If any value failed to be instantiated, null mock object placed by that key. That way we not have to call instantiator repetitively just to check that value is still can't be instantiated.

New types introduced:
InstantiationData - data necessary for instantiating new value. if value is currently null, if it is related or not, and set of already locked keys
ValueInstantiator - functional interface, producing values by key and instantiation data object
InstantiationResultType - enum will possible instantiation result types, created value, null value, instantiating postponed due to lacking of related values
InstantiationResult - object with instantiation result, contains result type and value, if provided

Merge branch 'impl-endless-field-server-app' into impl-endless-field-client-app

Websocket messages sending buffering

async.sendText() is not thread safe. That is, you can't send new message, if previous was not yet sent. So we have to implement queue.

ActionEndpoint onMessage handler

Endpoint receives message, deserialize it into ClientMessage instance, gets corresponding EndlessFieldAction instance from field.actionInvoker, locks chunks, performs action and constucts ActionServerMessage to broadcast. Then iterates over all chunks, affected by this message and sends serialized ActionServerMessage to all endpoints, which have given chunks in their scopes.

ActionServerMessage contains affected cells, origin cell, and userId and userName of player, who initiated this message.

ActionEndpointMessage renamed to ServerMessage. Its descendants renamed accordingly

UserId parameter added to InitServerMessage.

Clients scopes map values are now ActionEndpoint instances instead of user ids

Because we need action endpoints and their websocket sessions to broadcast messages by chunk ids.

ClientMessage class describes message received from user with /action websocket

Message has type and cell, where it has to be performed on.

EntryLockingConcurrentHashMap.lockKey() methods were renamed to lockEntry().

EndlessField.updateEntries method signature changed

Method accepts Map<CellPosition, ? extends EndlessFieldCell> instead of Map<CellPosition, T>. This is necessary because classes, which operates instances of specific EndlessField implementation can't know its exact type and it's type parameter. That's why cells has to be casted somewhere. Typecast on method call EndlessField<?> is unchecked, so we have to cast every cell explicitly within the method.

EndlessFieldArea class, which describes rectangle of cells in EndlessField

Class implements Iterable<CellPosition> interface, so it's instance may be used as parameter for EndlessFieldMethods, such as getEntries(Iterable<CellPosition> positions)

Mechanism of actions, which may be performed on the endless field
EndlessField instance has actionInvoker field (instance of EndlessFieldActionInvoker class), which is used to get action (instance of EndlessFieldAction interface) to perform by identifier. Action has methods to lock necessary chunks and to perform action itself. Specific actions set implemented as enum, which implements EndlessFieldAction. Every item of this enum has field of EndlessFieldActionBehaviour class, which contains actual action logic.
